sentences: Sam McPheeters (born 1969 Lorain, Ohio) is an American artist, journalist, novelist, and performer.
In 1985, McPheeters grew active with the hardcore punk scene, producing several fanzines and organizing local concerts.
After moving to New York City in 1987, he co-founded Born Against in 1989 and the Vermiform Records label in 1990.

In 2016, Talos Press release McPheeters' second novel, Exploded View.
In 2020 Sam's third book (an anti-memoir), "Mutations: The Many Strange Faces of Hardcore Punk", was published by Rare Bird Books.
